# NGC — GitHub Pages for all projects

**Policy (Ryan, 2026-07-11):** Always use **GitHub Pages** for opening any project.

## Canonical site

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| **Open here** | https://ngc4160.github.io/NGC-Brain/ |
| **Repo** | `NGC4160/NGC-Brain` |
| **Deploy branch / env** | GitHub Pages (`gh-pages` / `github-pages` environment) |
| **Base path** | `/NGC-Brain/` |

## Required behavior

When building, updating, or handing off any **openable** project (dashboard, form, checklist, tool, landing page, preview):

1. **Ship to GitHub Pages** — deploy so it is reachable under `https://ngc4160.github.io/NGC-Brain/…`
2. **Give Ryan the Pages URL** as the primary way to open it — not `localhost`, not `file://`, not a Cursor-only preview link
3. **Reuse the existing deploy path** when one exists (e.g. `.github/workflows/deploy-pages.yml`, `npm run build:pages`, `VITE_BASE_PATH=/NGC-Brain/`)
4. For **static HTML** tools, publish under a stable path (e.g. `/NGC-Brain/docs/…`) and confirm the live URL returns 200
5. After deploy, **verify** the live link before telling Ryan it is ready

## Do not

- Tell Ryan to “open localhost” or a local file as the main access method
- Host NGC shop tools on a different public host unless Ryan explicitly asks
- Leave a web project only in a PR branch without a Pages URL when the ask was to open/use it

Local `npm run dev` is fine for agent development. Handoff to Ryan/Christine/techs = **Pages URL**.

